Text.string: Quit dyin' already and buy a better shield!
Get the fun shots for your gunshots, at Dr. Zed's portable clinic!
Tired of wastin' cash on respawns? Look no further.
Buy from Zed, before you're dead.
Dr. Zed here, selling shields, mods, and peace of mind. Pieces of brain too, if you're buyin'.
If you want the skills to get the kills, you need a class mod.
Zed's Meds, baby. Zed's Meds.
Need a diagnosis? Go see a real doctor. Need healin'? Come see me!
Too much money and not enough blood? You're at the right place.
Dyin's for suckers and psychos; try Dr. Zed's Insta-Health!
When you need a dose of the red stuff, come find me.
Welcome to Dr. Zed's Mods and Meds!
Buy yourself a mod: for the merc with class.
You can't have too much health and shields—buy some today! Heck, buy some now!
I ain't a real doctor, but that don't stop my meds from workin'.
Come on back the next time you're dyin'!
Don't get shot TOO much now!
When you're shot tomorrow, you'll wish you'd spent more today.
Yep, we're done here.
If you're waiting for a lollipop, well, wait somewhere else!
You can see yourself out, I'm sure.
It's dangerous to go alone.||—Well, see ya.
Come see me again—you won't regret it.
Zed's Meds: “If you ain't buyin', you're dyin'.”
Long as you got a pulse and a bank account, you're welcome back any time.
That oughta do it—for now, at least.
Leavin' already? Well, it's your funeral! Heh-heh!
Come back soon, if you're still kickin'.
Y'all take care now!
Go on now, git!
Good as new! Which is not to say those are new, heh-heh.
Did the best I could—couldn't fix the face, though.
You're all set. Till next time, anyway.
Good for what assails ya.
Try and stay outta trouble. Or don't, I ain't your mom!
Don't get too attached. You can't take it with you.
All right—now, you're sure this time, right?
If you're lookin' to haggle with my vending machines, you're gonna be disappointed.
That's all right, I didn't want your trash anyhow. 'Less you're actually sellin'.
That's okay, lotsa folks are scared of commitment these days.
Best equip that soon, or drink it, or whatever. What'd you buy again?
The best money can buy.
That oughta keep you above ground for a while.
That'll make you feel right as rain. Whatever that is.
I should probably warn ya, that don't come with a warranty.
If anyone asks, you got that off a dead guy.
Who needs insurance when you got good gear?
Stay alive with this one item! Doctors hate it! Real ones, anyway.
Beats payin' for a New-U!
Might wanna rinse that off first.
If the board knew I was selling that, they'd have my license! Again!
Now, I don't show this merch to just everybody...
This here's my favorite. For the next few minutes, at least.
Most doctors got a degree to pay off, but I pass those savings right to you!
Four outta five doctors wish they'd got this one first!
Fell off the back of a Vault Hunter, if ya catch my drift.
Your pal sold this off, figured you'd like a look.
This looks more like your style anyway.
One man's trash is another man's triage!
Strictly speakin', I'm supposed to sterilize these.
I'm sure this'll come in handy, somehow.
I'll just add this to the pile, shall I?
End of transaction!
Only too happy to take dead folks' loot off your hands.
Lemme lighten your load.
I'll put it to good use.
That's my final offer!||—Oh. Well, all right then!
Usually I deal in organs, but this is close enough.
Now, no one's gonna come looking for this, right?
Sure you don't want store credit instead?
I'll take anything off your hands, sooner or later.
Aw, for me? You shouldn't have.
Thanks! I like to keep these handy in case I run out of anaesthetic.
You know, I pulled one of these out of a patient once.
Mighty kind of you.
